Most engineers use :wq to save and exit a file.It works â€” but itâ€™s not always the best practice.

ðŸ”¹ :wq â€“ WRITE & QUIT

Forces a write to disk every time
Even when no changes were made
Updates file metadata (timestamps)
Can create noise in Git diffs and audits

ðŸ”¹ :x â€“ SAVE ONLY IF MODIFIED & QUIT 

Writes the file only when changes exist
